The paper discusses the problem of defining and measuring internationality of scientific journals, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer science and digital libraries (cs.DL). The authors propose a new metric for measuring internationality, which involves analyzing citation patterns and influence diffusion across geographic boundaries, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses unethical practices in journal publication, which could be categorized under cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber ethics (cs.CY).
